The metanephridia are located in the peristomium and the first chaetiger (
Fig. 6
). The nephridial duct is paired first and then becomes unpaired. The nephroporus is located between the basal radiolar lobes (
Fig. 5H
). In males, the sperm duct is located directly under the faecal groove (
Fig. 6C,D
).
